  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(19-22) The seven Manassite chieftains who went over to David on the eve of Saul’s last battle.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(19) There fell.—The regular term for desertion of one cause for another (2Kings 25:11).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(19) ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "There fell.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The regular term for desertion of one cause for another (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Kings 25:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "When he came with the Philistines.—(Comp. 1Samuel 29:2-11.) This verse is a summary of the narrative of 1Samuel 29:2 to 1Samuel 30:1.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "When he came with the Philistines",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".—(Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 29:2-11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) This verse is a summary of the narrative of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 29:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " to ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 30:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They helped them not.—David and his men helped not the Philistines. Perhaps the right reading is he helped them (‘azarām), not they helped them (‘azarûm).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "They helped them not.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—David and his men helped not the Philistines. Perhaps the right reading is he helped them (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "‘azarām",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), not they helped them (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "‘azarûm",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Upon advisement.—After deliberation (Proverbs 20:18).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Upon advisement.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—After deliberation (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 20:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To the jeopardy of our heads.—At the price of our heads (1Chronicles 11:19). By betraying us he will make his peace with his old master.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "To the jeopardy of our heads.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—At the price of our heads (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 11:19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). By betraying us he will make his peace with his old master.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
