    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And there fell some of Manasseh to David,.... Of the tribe of Manasseh; they took his part, and on his side, and joined him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "when he came with the Philistines against Saul to battle; which was a strong proof of their cordial attachment to him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but they helped them not: the Philistines; neither David nor his men, nor the Manassites that joined them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the lords of the Philistines, upon advisement; counsel taken among themselves: sent him away; that is, David and his men: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying, he will fall to his master Saul, to the jeopardy of our heads; meaning, that he would go off with his troops to Saul, and betray them into his hands, and with their heads make his peace with him, see 1 Samuel 29:4. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "saying, he will fall to his master Saul, to the jeopardy of our heads; meaning, that he would go off with his troops to Saul, and betray them into his hands, and with their heads make his peace with him, see ",
